<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Woman Found Guilty of 'Air Rage' </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CAMDEN, N.J. (AP) -- A woman who kicked a 12-year-old boy's seat  
aboard her flight, causing him to hit his head, has been found 
guilty of ``air rage.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Celeste Keenan, 37, of Shamong, was found guilty by a federal  
judge Wednesday of assaulting an individual aboard an aircraft in 
flight. The conviction carries a maximum six months in jail and a 
$5,000 fine. 
</P>
<P>
	During the trial, passengers testified that Keenan walked onto  
the Spirit Airlines flight from Florida to Atlantic City in July 
and sprayed the cabin area with perfume after complaining about an 
odor. 
</P>
<P>
	Another passenger said Keenan glared at her and called her  
``white trash.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Keenan later fell asleep and pressed her feet against the seat  
in front of her, which was occupied by the 12-year-old boy. 
</P>
<P>
	When he reclined, Keenan complained and gave the seat a ``mule  
kick'' that broke the chair, sandwiching the boy. The boy said 
Keenan told him, ``I'll kill you. I'll sue your family so bad, 
you'll be living in the street.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Sentencing was scheduled for December.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
