<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Escaped Prisoner Recaptured in Kan. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COUNCIL GROVE, Kan. (AP) -- A child killer who climbed a 10-foot  
fence to escape from a jail recreation yard was recaptured without 
incident early today, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	Law officers who had searched for Scotty Adam since Tuesday  
converged on an area south of town when he was spotted in a hilly, 
wooded area, said Scott Teeselink, spokesman for the Kansas Bureau 
of Investigation. 
</P>
<P>
	Dogs and a helicopter tracked Adam back into town and he was  
taken into custody without incident, Teeselink said. Adam was not 
armed, and authorities believe he was always near the jail in a 
wooded area dotted with abandoned farmhouses and outbuildings. 
</P>
<P>
	``He never got very far,'' Teeselink said. ``The important thing  
is to let people know that he's back in custody and it's safe 
again.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Adam, 24, had scaled a razor wire-topped fence at the Morris  
County Jail hours after he had been sentenced to nearly 42 years in 
prison for shaking to death the 16-month-old child of his 
girlfriend. 
</P>
<P>
	He escaped from the jail's recreation yard when he was allowed  
out to smoke a cigarette and deputies were diverted by a traffic 
accident in town, Sheriff R.J. Meierhoff said. 
</P>
<P>
	Adam originally was charged with first-degree murder in the 1998  
shaking death of Timothy Post. He pleaded guilty in August to 
second-degree murder and the judge on Tuesday doubled the 
recommended sentence to almost 42 years. 
</P>
<P>
	At the time of the boy's slaying, Adam was on parole after  
serving time for the 1993 stabbing death of a Kansas State 
University student. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
