<HEADLINE> Fina Aquitaine Bid To Close Oct. 15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PARIS (AP) -- France's stock market regulator on Thursday set a  
date of Oct. 15 for the closure of Total Fina's friendly takeover 
bid for rival oil giant Elf Aquitaine. 
</P>
<P>
	The Conseil des Marches Financiers, the regulatory group that  
sets the stock market calendar for takeover bids, announced the 
closing date in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
	On Sept. 13, Total Fina and Elf brought an acrimonious,  
weeks-long takeover fight to a close by agreeing to a friendly 
merger in which Total Fina sweetened its bid for Elf. 
</P>
<P>
	Total Fina is now offering 19 of its own shares for 13 Elf  
shares in a deal worth about 52.4 billion euros ($55 billion). Its 
earlier unsolicited offer, launched July 5, was a 4-for-3 share 
swap, which Elf then countered with its own bid for Total Fina. 



  	   	
</P>
