</P>
<P>
	SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Greg Vaughn hit his 42nd homer and the  
Cincinnati Reds held on to beat San Diego 4-3 last night to gain a 
game on both teams they're chasing in the playoff hunt. Cincinnati 
closed within 2 1/2 games of both Houston in the NL Central and the 
New York Mets in the wild-card race. Houston lost 3-2 at Pittsburgh 
and the Mets lost 5-2 at Atlanta. 

</P>
<P>
	AP NewsBrief by VINCENT K. WILLIS  




