<HEADLINE> Blackhawks Sign Anders Eriksson </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Defenseman Anders Eriksson ended his 20-day  
holdout and agreed to a one-year contract with the Chicago 
Blackhawks. 
</P>
<P>
	Eriksson, a 24-year-old defenseman, agreed to the deal  
Wednesday, general manager Bob Murray said. Published reports today 
quote team sources as saying the contract guarantees Eriksson 
$800,000 with performance bonuses that could add $300,000 to it. 
</P>
<P>
	The Blackhawks had offered a three-year contract worth $3  
million, but couldn't agree with Eriksson on money for a long-term 
deal. 
</P>
<P>
	Eriksson was acquired from Detroit last year along with  
first-round picks in 1999 and 2001 in a trade that sent Blackhawks 
captain Chris Chelios to the Red Wings. 
</P>
<P>
	The 6-foot-2, 220-pound native of Sweden played in 11 games with  
Chicago and had eight assists. Eriksson's best year was in 
1997-1998 with Detroit, where he scored 7 goals in 66 games and had 
14 assists. 
</P>
<P>
	Eriksson's signing leaves the Blackhawks with one player still  
holding out for a better deal. Murray said negotiations have 
resumed with defenseman Boris Mironov's agent, but he had no 
progress to report. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
