<DOCNO> APW19990923.0079 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-23 16:40:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Keeneland Yearling Sale Sets Marks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
        LEXINGTON, Ky. (AP) -- More money changed hands during Keeneland's  
September Yearling Sale than in any other yearling auction in the history 
of the thoroughbred industry. 
</P>
<P>
        When the 11-day auction ended late Thursday afternoon, gross  
sales totaled $233,075,800 topping the previous record of $175,932, 
000, set at Keeneland's two-day 1984 July Selected Yearling Sale. 
</P>
<P>
        This year's September total also was the second highest for  
a thoroughbred auction of any type. It was topped only by last year's 
November Breeding Stock Sale, where buyers spent $264,657,700 for 3, 
379 horses. 
</P>
<P>
        The previous record gross for the September sale was $169,811,  
800 set last year. 
</P>
<P>
        Many September sale records fell including average price, number  
of horses sold, highest price for a colt and highest price for a filly. 
</P>
<P>
        The average price increased for the seventh consecutive year  
to $77,357, up 30.3 percent from the previous record of $59,375 set 
last year. The median price was $30,000. 
</P>
<P>
        Keeneland sold 3,013 horses, an increase of 5.3 percent from  
2,860 last year. The previous record for number of horses sold at the 
September sale was 2,958, set in 1995. 
</P>
<P>
        Twenty-three horses brought $1 million or more, topped by the  
$3.9 million Sheik Mohammed al Maktoum paid for a bay colt by Kris 
S. out of Mr. P's Princess. The previous record of $2.3 million was 
set in 1997. 
</P>
<P>
        Demi O'Byrne paid a sale record for a filly when he bid $2  
million for a daughter of Storm Cat and Piquetnol. It topped the previous 
record of $1,450,000 set last year. 
</P>
<P>
        Before this year, only 17 horses sold for $1 million or more  
in the history of the September sale. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990923.0080 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-23 06:30:24 </DATE_TIME>
