<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Carter Relative Scalps Tickets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AMERICUS, Ga. (AP) -- Jimmy Carter's 75th birthday gala is such a  
popular event that one of his relatives is accused of trying to 
scalp a ticket. 
</P>
<P>
	Lewis Patrick Harrison Jr. was arrested Saturday on charges he  
sold a ticket to the sold-out event for $500 to an undercover agent 
with the Georgia Bureau of Investigation, Sheriff Randy Howard 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Harrison, who paid $50 for the ticket to the Oct. 1 event,  
placed an ad in a local shopper offering tickets to the gala. 
</P>
<P>
	Harrison is Sybil Carter's nephew. Mrs. Carter is the widow of  
the former president's younger brother, Billy. 
</P>
<P>
	Harrison, who was charged with misdemeanor ticket scalping, was  
released on $1,000 bond Monday, a sheriff's department spokeswoman 
said Wednesday. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
