</P>
<P>
	Residents said victims were tortured and hung from meat hooks  
before they were decapitated, dismembered and thrown into the well. 
</P>
<P>
	At the United Nations in New York, Indonesian Foreign Minister  
Ali Alatas rejected suggestions for an international investigation 
into possible war crimes, saying Indonesia itself should first look 
into allegations of human rights violations. 
</P>
<P>
	In Dili, peacekeepers drove armored personnel carriers down the  
devastated streets, searching for anyone who looked suspicious. 
Within 24 hours, the soldiers had rounded up dozens of suspected 
militants and confiscated hundreds of guns, knives and machetes. 
</P>
<P>
	``We have lost count of the number of weapons,'' Evans said.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
