<CATEGORY> weather </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	The remnants of Hurricane Hilary produced showers and  
thunderstorms across California and into Arizona on Thursday while 
much of the rest of the nation was clear and dry. 
</P>
<P>
	Showers pushed by Hilary's winds spread north through central  
California and east into northern Arizona. The most rainfall 
reported in the lower 48 states on Thursday was about a half inch 
at the Grand Canyon. 
</P>
<P>
	A cold front pushed southeast across Washington state and into  
Idaho, bringing clouds and scattered showers to much of the 
Northwest. 
</P>
<P>
	Another cold front stretching from northern Michigan and across  
Wisconsin and southern Minnesota was making its way across the 
Great Lakes, pushing occasional hail and wind gusts into parts of 
Michigan and northern Illinois. 
</P>
<P>
	Clear to partly cloudy skies covered much of the rest of the  
nation. Most of the Northeast, Mid-Atlantic and Southeast and 
Plains was sunny and dry. 
</P>
<P>
	Highs across the Lower 48 on Thursday ranged from 87 degrees in  
Fort Lauderdale, Fla., to 29 degrees in Stanley, Idaho. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
