<HEADLINE> Chiquita To Cut Up to 200 Jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CINCINNATI (AP) -- Chiquita Brands International Inc. plans to  
eliminate as many as 200 jobs during the next several months to 
save at least $15 million a year in operating costs, management 
said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	The jobs are to be cut in corporate and staff ranks in the  
United States and Latin America, as well as banana operations in 
North America and Europe. 
</P>
<P>
	The reductions will cost the company $6 million before taxes in  
the third quarter to cover severance expenses, benefits extensions 
and job placement services, the Cincinnati-based company said. 
</P>
<P>
	Chiquita's earnings have lagged because of weak third-quarter  
sales of bananas in Europe. 
</P>
<P>
	The company has protested seven years of European Union limits  
on banana imports. The World Trade Organization judged the quotas 
to be illegal and authorized the United States to impose $191 
million of punitive tariffs on European goods. 
</P>
<P>
	Chiquita, best known as a banana exporter, also produces and  
distributes other fruits, vegetables and processed foods. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
