<HEADLINE> Lucent, Qualcomm in Wireless Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MURRAY HILL, N.J. (AP) -- Telecommunications giant Lucent  
Technologies Inc. today announced an alliance with Qualcomm Inc. to 
build wireless network equipment that offers faster speeds and more 
capacity. 
</P>
<P>
	Qualcomm will provide the core chip and software for use in  
Lucent's base station equipment, the companies said in a statement. 
The equipment will use Qualcomm's code division multiple access 
digital technology, or CDMA. 
</P>
<P>
	The companies said the improved transmission rates will  
accelerate the commercialization of wireless services such as 
video-on-demand and high-speed data delivery. 
</P>
<P>
	The Murray Hill, N.J.-based Lucent is a leading maker of  
telecommunications equipment with annual revenue of about $36 
billion. Qualcomm is a San Francisco-based wireless communications 
company, with revenue of about $108.5 million in 1998. 


  	   	
