<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Seekers Story </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATOP CARR MOUNTAIN, N.H. (AP) -- In a Sept. 13 story about a  
group of citizens who search for missing people, The Associated 
Press reported erroneously that a plane that crashed in New 
Hampshire in 1968 was an Eastern Airlines jet. 
</P>
<P>
	It was a Northeast Airlines turboprop, according to the National  
Transportation Safety Board. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
