<HEADLINE>  Students Protest in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) -- Thousands of university students  
rampaged in more than a half-dozen Indonesian cities today, 
clashing with police in protests against a new law giving the armed 
forces sweeping emergency powers. 
</P>
<P>
	Local news media, including radio station Sonora, reported three  
demonstrators were killed in Jakarta, but there was no confirmation 
from authorities or local hospitals. 
</P>
<P>
	A total of 53 people were injured, the SCTV network reported. At  
least four were rushed to the hospital with bullet wounds. 
</P>
<P>
	The protesters claim the new law will strengthen the military's  
already powerful role in domestic politics, and threaten the giant 
country's move toward democracy. 
</P>
<P>
	The clashes sent the Indonesian currency into a dive on fears of  
