<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Disney Names Board Vice Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BURBANK, Calif. (AP) -- Walt Disney executive Sanford Litvack has  
been named a vice chairman of the entertainment company's board. 
</P>
<P>
	Litvack, 63, has been senior executive vice president and chief  
of corporate operations for Disney since 1994 and was named to the 
company's board in 1995. He joins Roy Disney as a vice chairman. 
</P>
<P>
	``Sandy has been my key adviser over the past five years and has  
been invaluable in providing me with guidance and counsel,'' Disney 
Chairman Michael Eisner said Thursday in a news release announcing 
the appointment. 
</P>
<P>
	Most of the corporate staff will report to Litvack, while  
leaders of Disney's business units will continue to report to 
Eisner, the company said. 
</P>
<P>
	Litvack joined Disney in 1991 as senior vice president and  
general counsel. He was named executive vice president later that 
year and executive in charge of human resources in 1992. 
</P>
<P>
	Before joining Disney, Litvack headed the litigation department  
at the law firm of Dewey Ballantine. He also ran the antitrust 
division of the U.S. Justice Department during the Carter 
administration. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
