<HEADLINE> Raptors Sign Muggsy Bogues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORONTO (AP) -- Muggsy Bogues said his decision to sign with the  
Toronto Raptors was not a difficult one. 
</P>
<P>
	Bogues signed a one-year contract Thursday with the Raptors,  
reportedly worth $1 million, the minimum for an NBA player with 10 
or more seasons of experience. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's all about winning, attitude and preparing yourself,'' the  
5-foot-3 Bogues said. ``Guys like (Charles) Oakley, Kevin Willis, 
Antonio Davis, Dell Curry, Dee Brown, Vince Carter and Tracy 
McGrady, they're all quality people. I like what the Raptors are 
doing and that was a very easy decision.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Bogues, a 12-year NBA veteran, averaged 5.1 points and 3.7  
assists per game in 36 regular-season games last year with the 
Golden State Warriors. 
</P>
<P>
	``Muggsy has always been a very exciting player in this league  
and our fans will really enjoy watching him,'' said Raptors general 
manager Glen Grunwald. ``He brings veteran experience to the team 
at the point-guard position and we feel that he and Alvin Williams 
will make a great tandem, combining youth and experience and both 
bringing great athleticism.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Bogues was a first-round selection (12th overall) by the  
Washington Bullets in 1987. In his NBA career, Bogues has averaged 
8 points and 8 assists in 806 games and is the league's career 
leader in assist-to-turnover ratio (4.69). 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
