<HEADLINE> Lucent, Qualcomm in Wireless Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MURRAY HILL, N.J. (AP) -- Lucent Technologies Inc. on Thursday  
announced an alliance with Qualcomm Inc. to build wireless network 
equipment that offers faster speeds and more capacity. 
</P>
<P>
	Qualcomm will provide the core chip and software for use in  
Lucent's base station equipment, the companies said in a statement. 
The equipment will use Qualcomm's code division multiple access 
digital technology, or CDMA. 
</P>
<P>
	The companies said the improved transmission rates will  
accelerate the commercialization of wireless video and data 
services. 
</P>
<P>
	Lucent, based in Murray Hill, N.J., is a leading maker of  
telecommunications equipment with annual revenue of about $36 
billion. Qualcomm is a San Diego-based wireless technology company, 
with revenue of about $3.3 billion. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
