<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Fox Appeals Ruling on Turner Suit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- Fox Sports Net South is appealing a lower court  
ruling that allowed Turner South, a new regional network, to 
broadcast Atlanta baseball, football and hockey games. 
</P>
<P>
	Earlier this month, Fulton County Superior Court Judge Rowland  
Barnes denied Fox Sports' request for an injunction. The network 
was attempting to prevent Turner South from including the 
Thrashers, Hawks and Braves as part of its programming lineup, 
beginning Oct. 1. 
</P>
<P>
	Fox filed its appeal Thursday with the Georgia Supreme Court and  
said in a statement that it ``intends to pursue all legal and 
equitable remedies available.'' 
</P>
<P>
	No date has been set for a briefing in the matter, at which the  
court would decide whether to grant Fox's appeal a hearing. 
</P>
<P>
	Fox sued in June, claiming that the new network violates a  
12-year non-compete agreement that was part of a $65 million deal 
the companies struck in 1996. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
