<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Charges Dismissed in Cisneros Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LUBBOCK, Texas (AP) -- Conspiracy charges have been dismissed  
against a Texas couple being prosecuted by the independent counsel 
investigating charges against ex-Housing Secretary Henry Cisneros. 
</P>
<P>
	U.S. District Judge Sam Cummings dismissed charges Wednesday  
against Patsy and Allen Wooten. 
</P>
<P>
	The Wootens were accused of falsely obtaining a bank mortgage  
for Mrs. Wooten's sister, Linda Jones, Cisneros' former mistress 
who was at the center of the charges against the former Clinton 
Cabinet member. 
</P>
<P>
	The Wootens pleaded guilty in January 1998 to one count each of  
conspiracy to commit bank fraud and making false statements to a 
bank. They had never been sentenced. 
</P>
<P>
	In the motion to dismiss the charges, independent counsel David  
Barrett said the action was being done because of the Wootens' 
cooperation and good conduct since their pleas. 
</P>
<P>
	``I was pleasantly surprised when all the parties agreed to a  
dismissal,'' Mrs. Wooten told the Lubbock Avalanche-Journal in a 
telephone interview Wednesday night. ``We just hope it's all behind 
us now. My husband and I run around and pinch each other just to 
ask, `Is it really over?''' 
</P>
<P>
	Cisneros was charged with lying to the FBI about payments he  
made to Ms. Jones following their highly publicized affair. He 
avoided 18 felony charges by accepting a plea agreement the day his 
trial was to begin. 
</P>
<P>
	Cisneros admitted lying to the FBI and received a misdemeanor  
conviction. He must pay a $10,000 fine but faces no jail time or 
probation. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Jones pleaded guilty in 1998 to 28 charges of bank fraud,  
money laundering and lying to federal investigators and received a 
3 1/2-year prison sentence. She was released last week, after Cummings 
reduced the sentence at Barrett's request. 
</P>
<P>
	According to court documents, Ms. Jones was released early  
because of her cooperation in the Cisneros case. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
