<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Pan American Basketball Coach Fired </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EDINBURG, Texas (AP) -- Delray Brooks officially became a fired  
coach when Texas-Pan American officials denied the appeal of his 
dismissal. 
</P>
<P>
	On Wednesday, James Langabeer, Texas-Pan American's vice  
president for business affairs, upheld athletic director Bill 
Weidner's decision to fire Brooks late last month. 
</P>
<P>
	Langabeer's decision came four days after a termination hearing  
was held for Brooks. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's unfortunate,'' Brooks said Wednesday night. ``I haven't  
done anything wrong. Unfortunately, it has come to that. The ones 
that have suffered the most are the players. This has taken a lot 
out of me and my family. It's an unfortunate set of circumstances 
in which I haven't done anything wrong.'' 
</P>
<P>
	A news conference was scheduled Friday during which the school  
is to hire a replacement. The (McAllen) Monitor reported Thursday 
that Bob Hoffman of Oklahoma Baptist was expected to be hired. 
</P>
<P>
	Brooks was fired on Aug. 23 because school officials believe  
that he deposited a check from Southwest Missouri State for $25,000 
into his personal account and then made withdrawals from the 
account. 
</P>
<P>
	During the hearing, Brooks acknowledged that $25,000 was placed  
in his account last December, but denied that he deposited it or 
that he told someone else to do so. 
</P>
<P>
	In a letter obtained by The Monitor, Langabeer wrote to Brooks'  
lawyer saying the coach didn't produce convincing evidence as to 
who might have deposited the check and also noted that Brooks did 
not return the money. 
</P>
<P>
	Hidalgo County District Attorney Rene Guerra has said he will  
seek a grand jury indictment against Brooks. 
</P>
<P>
	Brooks played at Indiana and Providence, and was an assistant  
for five years at Kentucky before being hired by Texas-Pan American 
in 1997. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
