<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Glance at Tech Group Purchasing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Some states have tried to guide software content by taking bids  
and making purchases statewide. A survey of states by Education 
Week shows that 23 states have a group-purchasing program for 
instructional software in which all schools can participate: 
</P>
<P>
	Arkansas, Colorado, Florida, Georgia, Idaho, Illinois, Indiana,  
Iowa, Kentucky, Louisiana, Michigan, Mississippi, Missouri,Nevada, 
New Hampshire, New Jersey, Ohio, Oregon, Tennessee, Texas, Utah, 
Washington and West Virginia. 

</P>
<P>
	Eight states have developed their own learning materials for the  
Web: Florida, Hawaii, Indiana, Iowa, North Carolina, Ohio, South 
Dakota and Utah. 
</P>
<P>
	Four states have developed their own educational software:  
California, Florida, Iowa, and Ohio. 
  	   	
</P>
