<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Pirates Call Up Brown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- The Pittsburgh Pirates recalled outfielder Emil  
Brown from Triple-A Nashville on Thursday to replace Brian Giles, 
who is out for the rest of the season with a broken finger. 
</P>
<P>
	Giles developed into one of the NL's best power hitters, batting  
.315 with 39 homers and 115 RBIs. But he broke the middle finger on 
his right hand sliding into second base Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Brown hit .307 with 20 doubles, 18 home runs and 60 RBIs in 110  
games at Nashville. He also stole 16 bases. 
</P>
<P>
	The Pirates also activated left-hander Jason Christiansen from  
the 15-day disabled list. Christiansen has been suffering from neck 
and back pain and hasn't played since July 28, though he did pitch 
two scoreless innings in two rehab outings at Nashville. 
</P>
<P>
	He is 2-3 with three saves and a 4.46 ERA in 34 1-3 innings of  
relief. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
