<HEADLINE> Sabres Sign Center Barnes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BUFFALO, N.Y. (AP) -- The Buffalo Sabres signed center Stu Barnes  
on Thursday, leaving five players unsigned as the regular season 
approaches. 
</P>
<P>
	Terms were not disclosed. Barnes, acquired from Pittsburgh in  
March, scored seven playoff goals as the Sabres advanced to the 
Stanley Cup finals. Barnes came to training camp without a contract 
and has one goal in three preseason games. 
</P>
<P>
	``Every move for me has been a positive thing,'' he said.  
``Hopefully we can get back to the Stanley Cup finals.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Sabres are still missing Miroslav Satan, last season's  
leading scorer, center Curtis Brown, right wing Vaclav Varada and 
defensemen Rhett Warrener and Jay McKee. 
</P>
<P>
	``It shows that there's some movement now,'' coach Lindy Ruff  
said. ``The other guys might follow.'' 
  	   	
</P>
