<HEADLINE> Sosa Remakes Jordan's Restaurant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Though Michael Jordan retired his Bulls jersey  
just eight months ago, his restaurant is being remade to honor 
Chicago's newest sports star: Sammy Sosa. 
</P>
<P>
	The popularity of Michael Jordan's Restaurant is slipping,  
though it remains profitable, said H. Gene Silverberg, a 
controlling partner. He complained that Jordan seldom eats at the 
restaurant, located just north of downtown Chicago. 
</P>
<P>
	In its place will be Sammy Sosa's Restaurant, and Jordan's spot  
will be moved to a smaller location, Silverberg said. 
</P>
<P>
	Silverberg said he envisions a ``Cubs restaurant starring Sammy  
Sosa, the best show in town with the No. 1 star possible.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Apparently the switch is being made without Jordan's approval --  
Silverberg said he doesn't need it. 
</P>
<P>
	Sosa's restaurant will take over Jordan's spot by the opening of  
next baseball season, Silverberg said. 
</P>
<P>
	And Sosa, unlike Jordan, will be required to make appearances at  
the restaurant, he said. 
  	   	
</P>
