<HEADLINE> Hearing Date Set for Boxer Vargas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SANTA BARBARA, Calif. (AP) -- A preliminary hearing date of Nov.  
3 was set Thursday for unbeaten International Boxing Federation 
junior middleweight champion Fernando Vargas and four others who 
face assault charges. 
</P>
<P>
	Vargas, 21, and the others are charged with assault with a  
deadly weapon and conspiracy to commit a crime stemming from a July 
25 altercation at a home in Summerland, located just outside Santa 
Barbara. 
</P>
<P>
	Conviction could carry a prison term of almost eight years.  
</P>
<P>
	``Basically, everyone appeared in court today -- all the lawyers,  
all the defendants -- and the hearing date was set,'' deputy 
district attorney Hilary Dozer said. 
</P>
<P>
	The hearing will be held in Superior Court before judge Joseph  
Lodge. 
</P>
<P>
	The men are accused of beating Doug Rossi, 23, who broke up a  
fight between Vargas and a woman's ex-boyfriend at her apartment. 
Vargas claimed he was out of the room when the alleged assault took 
place. 
</P>
<P>
	Vargas, from Oxnard, Calif., has maintained his innocence.  
</P>
<P>
	``On Nov. 3, the judge will be able to evaluate the evidence  
which will be presented to support the charges, and if he feels 
there is enough evidence, the matter will be shortly thereafter set 
for trial,'' Dozer said. ``I believe the evidence which will be 
heard at the hearing will generate a sufficient reason for the case 
to eventually be tried by a jury here in Santa Barbara.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Charged along with Vargas are his cousin, Ernesto Vargas, 27;  
Carlos Lopez, 28; Freddie Flores, 21, and Vincent Arenas, 20. 
</P>
<P>
	Eight days before the incident, Vargas improved his record to  
17-0, with 17 knockouts, by successfully defending his title 
against Raul Marquez. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
