<HEADLINE> European Bank Leaves Rates Unchanged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FRANKFURT, Germany (AP) -- The European Central Bank left its key  
lending rate unchanged at 2.5 percent on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	The ECB governing council's decision, which analysts had  
expected, applies to the 11 nations that introduced the euro 
currency on Jan. 1. 
</P>
<P>
	The bank dropped the rate half a percentage point in April, its  
only change since taking over monetary policy for the euro bloc. 
</P>
<P>
	At the time, it urged European governments to look less to the  
central bank and enact structural reforms to spur growth and lower 
unemployment. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
