<HEADLINE> NBA To Start Its Own TV Channel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	VANCOUVER, British Columbia (AP) -- The NBA plans to launch its  
own 24-hour television channel, a venture called NBA.com TV 
featuring statistics, scores and news, live studio-based 
programming and shots of games in progress. 
</P>
<P>
	The channel also will broadcast classic NBA games, videos and  
basketball-related movies. It will be available beginning Nov. 2 on 
DirecTV and the pay-per-view outlet Viewer's Choice, the league 
announced Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Regular season and playoff games will continue to be broadcast  
on NBC, Turner Sports and regional affiliates. 
</P>
<P>
	``We see this as an opportunity to tap into the rich array of  
information available on NBA.com and the vast television 
programming from our video and film library,'' said Adam Silver, 
president of NBA Entertainment. 
  	   	
</P>
