<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Lukas, Baffert Battle for Supremacy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FLORENCE, Ky. (AP) -- With two victories apiece, trainers D.  
Wayne Lukas and Bob Baffert battle Saturday for supremacy in the 
Kentucky Cup. 
</P>
<P>
	Baffert's Horse, Classic Cat, is the favorite at 7-5 over Lukas'  
Cat Thief, 9-5, in the $500,000 Kentucky Cup Classic at Turfway 
Park. 
</P>
<P>
	``These are two marquee horses, and I just gave the edge to  
Classic Cat because of his age and experience,'' Mike Battaglia, 
who makes the morning line at Turfway Park, said. 
</P>
<P>
	Both horses have been on the fringe of stardom.  
</P>
<P>
	Classic Cat, a 4-year-old, finished third in the Preakness last  
year when Baffert won with Real Quiet. Cat Thief, a 3-year-old, was 
third in the Kentucky Derby this year when Lukas won with 
Charismatic. 
</P>
<P>
	Classic Cat's last win was in the San Bernardino Handicap at  
Santa Anita in April. He has won nearly $1.2 million in 16 starts. 
</P>
<P>
	Cat Thief last won in the Swaps at Hollywood Park in July. His  
earnings total $1.3 million in 17 starts. 
</P>
<P>
	The Kentucky Cup Classic is part of Turfway Park's $1.15 million  
Kentucky Cup Day of Champions, which includes three other graded 
stakes. Past winners include Tabasco Cat and Thunder Gulch, trained 
by Lukas, and Semoran and Silver Charm, trained by Baffert. 
</P>
<P>
	This year's race looked like it would be a small field, with  
only five confirmed starters before four more entries came in just 
before Thursday's draw for post positions. 
</P>
<P>
	``Maybe trainers were looking at the short field and decided to  
jump in,'' Battaglia said. ``If they were thinking it would be 
easy, I think they were dead wrong.'' 
</P>
<P>
	After Classic Cat and Cat Thief, Battaglia made the entry of  
Truluck and Social Charter the third choice at 3-1. 
</P>
<P>
	The field, from the rail out, with jockeys and morning line odds  
for the $500,000 Kentucky Cup Classic: 
</P>
<P>
	Cat Thief, Pat Day, 9-5; Night Dreamer, Chris McCarron, 10-1;  
Part the Waters, Danny Gonter, 20-1; (e) Social Charter, Shane 
Sellers, 3-1; Classic Cat, David Flores, 7-5; Da Devil, Calvin 
Borel, 20-1; Well Noted, Marlon St. Julien, 30-1; Blazing Sword, 
Willie Martinez, 15-1; (e) Truluck, Robby Albarado, 3-1. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
