<HEADLINE> Nets Send Murdock to Clippers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- The New Jersey Nets traded backup  
point guard Eric Murdock to the Los Angeles Clippers on Thursday 
for veteran small forward Johnny Newman. 
</P>
<P>
	The stint with the Nets will be the second for Newman, who  
averaged 6.1 points in 50 games with Cleveland last season. The 
14-year veteran was traded with Derek Anderson to the Clippers for 
Lamont Murray after the season. 
</P>
<P>
	Newman averaged 9.5 points and 1.9 rebounds for New Jersey in  
1993-94 after being acquired in a deal that sent Rumeal Robinson to 
Charlotte. 
</P>
<P>
	Murdock appeared in only 15 games in last year's  
lockout-shortened season because of an injury to his left knee. He 
averaged 7.9 points and 4.4 assists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
